title: Blackwater National Wildlife Refuge : Narrative report : September, October, November and December, 1945
name: blackwater-national-wildlife-refuge-narrative-report-september-october-november-and-dece-1-93ca7
notes: This narrative report for Blackwater NWR outlines Refuge accomplishments from September through December of 1945. The report begins by summarizing the weather conditions and water conditions during this period. Wildlife- including migratory birds, upland game birds, big game animals, furbearers, predators, rodents, mammals, raptors, and fish- is also covered. The Refuge development and maintenance section discusses physical developments and plantings. Resource management is outlined; topics include fur harvesting. A progress report on field investigations and applied research is also provided. The public relations section of the report describes Refuge visitors. Items of interest and N-R forms are attached.
